Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Mix cracker crumbs, oregano, garlic powder, paprika and pepper in shallow dish. Coat chicken with hot pepper sauce, then dip in crumb mixture, turning to evenly coat both sides of each wing piece. Place in single layer on greased baking sheet. Bake 35 to 40 min. or until golden brown and cooked through (180 degrees F), turning pieces over after 20 min. Serve warm.